ark\n| note11   = [[Wideboys]] in the Shadows Vocal Mix\n| extra11  = {{hlist|The Alias|Ryden|Wideboys <small>(add.)</small>}}\n| length11 = 3:45\n\n| title12  = Story of a Heart\n| note12   = 7th Heaven Radio Mix\n| extra12  = {{hlist|The Alias|7th Heaven <small>(add.)</small>}}\n| length12 = 3:33\n\n| total_length = 44:54\n}}\n\n'''Notes'''\n*\"You Make Me Whole\" is a cover of the song originally performed by [[Aneta Sablik]].<ref>http://hitparade.ch/song/Aneta/You-Make-Me-Whole-1292015</ref>\n*\"Story of a Heart\" is a cover of the song originally performed by [[Benny Anderssons orkester|Benny Andersson's solo band]].<ref name=\"Metro 1\">{{cite web|last=Waring|first=Olivia|url=http://metro.co.uk/2017/03/06/steps-are-returning-with-a-total-banger-thanks-to-abbas-benny-andersson-and-bjorn-ulvaeus-6490115/|title=Steps are returning with a total banger thanks to Abba\u2019s Benny Andersson and Bjorn Ulvaeus|work=[[Metro (British newspaper)|Metro]]|date=6 March 2017|accessdate=8 March 2017}}</ref>\n*\"No More Tears on the Dancefloor\" is a cover of the [[Thomas Anders|Anders]]|[[J\u00f6rn-Uwe Fahrenkrog-Petersen|Fahrenkrog]] song.<!-- \"Anders|Fahrenkrog\" That is how it is spelled. With the | between the names.  -->\n*\"I Will Love Again\" is a cover of the song originally performed by [[Lara Fabian]].<ref name=\"Tears on the Dancefloor Credits\"/>\n\n==Charts and certifications==\n{{col-begin}}\n{{col-2}}\n\n===Weekly charts===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|-\n! scope=\"col\"| Chart (2017)\n! scope=\"col\"| Peak<br>position\n|-\n{{album chart|Australia|46|artist=Steps|album=Tears on the Dancefloor|rowheader=true|accessdate=29 April 2017}}\n|-\n{{album chart|Flanders|20|artist=Steps|album=Tears on the Dancefloor|rowheader=true|accessdate=28 April 2017}}\n|-\n{{album chart|Ireland2|10|artist=Steps|rowheader=true|accessdate=28 April 2017}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| New Zealand Heatseeker Albums ([[Recorded Music NZ|RMNZ]])<ref>{{cite web|url=https://nztop40.co.nz/chart/albums?chart=4357#all_records_extra|title=NZ Heatseeker Albums Chart|publisher=[[Recorded Music NZ]]|date=28 April 2017|accessdate=28 April 2017}}</ref>\n| 10\n|-\n{{album chart|Scotland|1|date=20170428|rowheader=true|accessdate=29 April 2017}}\n|-\n{{album chart|UK|2|date=20170428|rowheader=true|accessdate=29 April 2017}}\n|-\n{{album chart|UKIndependent|1|date=20170428|rowheader=true|accessdate=29 April 2017}}\n|}\n{{col-2}}\n\n===Year-end charts===\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|-\n! scope=\"col\"| Chart (2017)\n! scope=\"col\"| Position\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| UK Albums (OCC)<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.officialcharts.com/charts/end-of-year-artist-albums-chart/|title=End of Year Album Chart Top 100 \u2013 2017|publisher=Official Charts Company|accessdate=10 January 2018}}</ref>\n| 59\n|}\n\n===Certifications===\n{{Certification Table Top}}\n{{Certification Table Entry|region=United Kingdom|title=Tears on the Dancefloor|artist=Steps|type=album|award=Gold|certyear=2017|relyear=2017|access-date=20 May 2017}}\n{{Certification Table Bottom}}\n{{col-end}}\n\n==''Crying at the Disco'' reissue==\n{{Infobox album\n| name       = Tears on the Dancefloor: Crying at the Disco\n| type       = Studio\n| longtype   = ([[reissue]])\n| artist     = [[Steps (group)|Steps]]\n| cover      = Steps - Crying at the Disco (Official Album Cover).jpeg\n| border     = yes\n| alt        = Head shots of five people with a mirrored, upside down reflection of themselves, with an alternate facial expression.\n| released   = {{Start date|2017|10|27|df=yes}}\n| recorded   = October 2016\u2013August 2017\n| venue      =\n| studio     =\n| genre      =\n| length     = {{Duration|m=49|s=36}}\n| label      = \n*Absolute\n*[[Fascination Records|Fascination]]\n| producer   = \n*The Alias\n*Carl Ryden\n*[[Brian Rawling]]\n*7th Heaven\n*Adam Turner\n*Club Junkies\n*Rescue Rangerz\n*Porl Young\n*DJ David\n*David Chamberlin\n*[[Gordon Pogoda]]\n*Gloria Sklerov\n| prev_title = Tears on the Dancefloor\n| prev_year  = 2017\n| next_title = [[Party on the Dancefloor]]\n| next_year  = 2018\n| misc       = {{Singles\n | name        = Tears on the Dancefloor: Crying at the Disco\n | type        = studio\n | single1     = [[Dancing with a Broken Heart#Steps version|Dancing with a Broken Heart]]\n | single1date = 19 September 2017\n}}\n}}\n\n'''''Tears on the Dancefloor: Crying at the Disco''''' is the [[reissue]] of British group [[Steps (group)|Steps]] fifth [[studio album]] ''Tears on the Dancefloor'' (2017),  with several new recordings. On 18 September 2017, Steps announced that the album would be reissued on 27 October with five new songs, including a Christmas track, as well as previously unreleased remixes of \"Happy\", \"Glitter & Gold\" and \"I Will Love Again\", and titled ''Tears on the Dancefloor: Crying at the Disco''.<ref name=\"OCC 3\">{{cite web|last=Copsey|first=Rob|url=http://www.officialcharts.com/chart-news/steps-to-re-release-their-latest-album-tears-on-the-dancefloor-with-five-new-songs__20450/|title=Steps to re-release their latest album Tears On The Dancefloor with five new songs|work=Official Charts Company|date=18 September 2017|accessdate=19 September 2017|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170919154138/http://www.officialcharts.com/chart-news/steps-to-re-release-their-latest-album-tears-on-the-dancefloor-with-five-new-songs__20450/|url-status=live|archivedate=19 September 2017}}</ref>\n\n===Track listing===\n{{Track listing\n| collapsed = no\n| headline = ''Tears on the Dancefloor (Crying At the Disco Deluxe Edition)''<ref name=\"iTunes Deluxe Album UK\">{{cite web|url=https://itunes.apple.com/album/tears-on-the-dancefloor-crying-at-the-disco-deluxe-edition/id1280401275?app=itunes|title=Tears On the Dancefloor (Crying At the Disco Deluxe Edition)|work=iTunes Store|accessdate=18 September 2017}}</ref>\n\n| extra_column = Producer(s)\n\n| title1   = [[Dancing with a Broken Heart#Steps version|Dancing with a Broken Heart]]\n| writer1  = {{hlist|[[Delta Goodrem]]|Vince Pizzinga|[[John Shanks]]}}\n| extra1   = Carl Ryden\n| length1  = 3:29\n\n| title2   = [[Scared of the Dark]]\n| writer2  = {{hlist|Carl Ryden|[[Fiona Bevan]]}}\n| extra2   = {{hlist|The Alias|Ryden}}\n| length2  = 3:46\n\n| title3   = September Sun\n| writer3  = {{hlist|Barry Stone|[[Julian Gingell]]}}\n| extra3   = The Alias\n| length3  = 4:19\n\n| title4   = [[Neon Blue]]\n| note4    = Radio Mix\n| writer4  = {{hlist|Ryden|Bevan}}\n| extra4   = {{hlist|The Alias|Ryden}}\n| length4  = 3:26\n\n| title5   = You Make Me Whole\n| writer5  = {{hlist|[[Ina Wroldsen]]|[[Wayne Hector]]|[[TMS (production team)|Ben Kohn, Tom Barnes & Pete Kelleher]]}}\n| extra5   = The Alias\n| length5  = 3:42\n\n| title6   = [[Story of a Heart (song)|Story of a Heart]]\n| writer6  = {{hlist|[[Benny Andersson]]|[[Bj\u00f6rn Ulvaeus]]}}\n| extra6   = The Alias\n| length6  = 4:16\n\n| title7   = Fool for You\n| writer7  = {{hlist|Ryden|Bevan}}\n| extra7   = Ryden\n| length7  = 3:31\n\n| title8   = Happy\n| writer8  = {{hlist|[[Steve Mac]]|Wroldsen}}\n| extra8   = The Alias\n| length8  = 3:37\n\n| title9   = No More Tears on the Dancefloor\n| writer9  = {{hlist|[[Carl Falk]]|[[Darren Hayes]]}}\n| extra9   = The Alias\n| length9  = 3:47\n\n| title10   = Beautiful Battlefield\n| writer10  = {{hlist|[[Gordon Pogoda]]|Gloria Sklerov|David Chamberlin}}\n| extra10   = {{hlist|David Chamberlin|[[Gordon Pogoda]]|Gloria Sklerov|The Alias}}\n| length10  = 3:21\n\n| title11   = Firefly\n| writer11  = {{hlist|Mac|Wroldsen}}\n| extra11   = The Alias\n| length11  = 3:26\n\n| title12   = Space Between Us\n| writer12  = {{hlist|Stone|Gingell}}\n| extra12   = The Alias\n| length12  = 4:16\n\n| title13   = Glitter & Gold\n| writer13  = {{hlist|Stone|Gingell}}\n| extra13   = The Alias\n| length13  = 3:36\n\n| title14  = [[I Will Love Again]]\n| writer14 = {{hlist|[[Mark Taylor (music producer)|Mark Taylor]]|[[Paul Barry (songwriter)|Paul Barry]]}}\n| extra14  = [[Brian Rawling]]\n| length14 = 3:44\n\n| total_length = 49:36\n}}\n{{Track listing\n| collapsed = yes\n| headline = Digital / Vinyl Bonus Tracks\n| extra_column = Producer(s)\n\n| title15   = Dear Santa\n| writer15  = {{hlist|Gingell|Stone|[[Una Healy]]}}\n| extra15   = The Alias\n| length15  = 3:03\n\n| title16   = Scared of the Dark\n| note16    = Acoustic\n| writer16  = {{hlist|Ryden|Bevan}}\n| extra16   = {{hlist|The Alias|Ryden}}\n| length16  = 4:01\n\n| title17   = Dancing With a Broken Heart \n| note17    = 7th Heaven Radio Mix\n| writer17  = {{hlist|Goodrem|Pizzinga|Shanks}}\n| extra17   = {{hlist|The Alias|7th Heaven}}\n| length17  = 3:29\n\n| title18   = Story of a Heart\n| note18    = 7th Heaven Radio Mix\n| writer18  = {{hlist|Andersson|Ulvaeus}}\n| extra18   = {{hlist|The Alias|7th Heaven}}\n| length18  = 3:33\n\n| title19   = Neon Blue\n| note19    = Adam Turner Radio Edit\n| writer19  = {{hlist|Ryden|Bevan}}\n| extra19   = {{hlist|The Alias|Ryden|Adam Turner}}\n| length19  = 4:05\n\n| title20   = Scared of the Dark\n| note20    = 7th Heaven Radio Mix\n| writer20  = {{hlist|Ryden|Bevan}}\n| extra20   = {{hlist|The Alias|Ryden|7th Heaven}}\n| length20  = 4:24\n\n| title21   = Happy\n| note21    = Club Junkies Radio Mix\n| writer21  = {{hlist|Mac|Wroldsen}}\n| extra21   = {{hlist|The Alias|Club Junkies}}\n| length21  = 3:37\n\n| title22   = Glitter & Gold\n| note22    = Rescue Rangerz Radio Mix\n| writer22  = {{hlist|Stone|Gingell}}\n| extra22   = {{hlist|The Alias|Rescue Rangerz}}\n| length22  = 4:00\n\n| title23  = I Will Love Again\n| note23   = Porl Young Radio Mix\n| writer23 = {{hlist|Taylor|Barry}}\n| extra23  = {{hlist|Rawling|Porl Young}}\n| length23 = 3:57\n\n| title24   = Tears on the Dancefloor\n| note24    = DJ David Strong 7th Heaven Medley\n| writer24  = {{hlist|Falk|Hayes}}\n| extra24   = {{hlist|The Alias|DJ David|7th Heaven}}\n| length24  = 7:19\n\n| total_length = 93:55\n}}\n\n'''Notes'''\n*\"Dancing with a Broken Heart\" is a cover of the song originally performed by [[Delta Goodrem]].\n*\"You Make Me Whole\" is a cover of the song originally performed by Zoe Zana<ref>{{Citation|title=You Make Me Whole|url=https://soundcloud.com/zoe-zana/you-make-me-whole|language=en|accessdate=2017-09-22}}</ref>  and later by [[Aneta Sablik]] & [[Anna Naklab]].\n*\"Story of a Heart\" is a cover of the song originally performed by [[Benny Anderssons orkester|Benny Andersson's solo band]].\n*\"No More Tears on the Dancefloor\" is a cover of the [[Thomas Anders|Anders]]|[[J\u00f6rn-Uwe Fahrenkrog-Petersen|Fahrenkrog]] song.<!-- \"Anders|Fahrenkrog\" That is how it is spelled. With the | between the names.  -->\n*\"I Will Love Again\" is a cover of the song originally performed by [[Lara Fabian]].\n*\"Tears on the Dancefloor\" is a medley of the 7th Heaven Remixes of \"Scared of the Dark\", \"Story of a Heart\", \"Neon Blue\" and \"Dancing with a Broken Heart\".\n\n===Charts===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|-\n! scope=\"col\"| Chart (2017)\n! scope=\"col\"| Peak<br>position\n|-\n{{album chart|Scotland|6|date=2017-11-09|rowheader=true|accessdate=29 November 2017}}\n|-\n{{album chart|UK|6|date=2017-11-09|rowheader=true|accessdate=29 November 2017}}\n|-\n{{album chart|UKIndependent|1|date=2017-11-09|rowheader=true|accessdate=29 November 2017}}\n|}\n\n==Release history==\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\"\n|+ List of release dates, showing country, format, label and references\n|-\n! scope=\"col\" | Country\n! scope=\"col\" | Date\n! scope=\"col\" | Format\n! scope=\"col\" | Label\n! scope=\"col\" | {{abbr|Ref.|References}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" rowspan=\"3\" | United Kingdom\n| rowspan=\"5\"| 21 April 2017\n| [[Music download|Digital download]]\n| rowspan=\"6\"| Steps Music LLP\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" | <ref name=\"UK Download Track listing Official Store\">{{cite web|url=https://store.stepsoffici