yle=\"text-align:center; color:#ccc;\"|WD\n|-\n|style=\"background:#EFEFEF;\" | [[Malta Cup|European Open]]<ref group=\"nb\">The event ran under different names such as European Open (1988/1989 to 1996/1997 and 2001/2002 to 2003/2004) and Irish Open (1998/1999).</ref>\n| style=\"text-align:center; color:#ccc;\"|NH\n|align=\"center\" style=\"background:#afeeee;\"|[[1989 European Open (snooker)|3R]]\n|align=\"center\" style=\"background:#afeeee;\"|[[1990 European Open (snooker)|2R]]\n|align=\"center\" style=\"background:#afeeee;\"|[[1991 European Open (snooker)|1R]]\n|align=\"center\" style=\"background:#ffebcd;\"|[[1992 European Open (snooker)|QF]]\n|align=\"center\" style=\"background:#afeeee;\"|[[1993 European Open (1992/1993)|2R]]\n| style=\"text-align:center; color:#ccc;\"|LQ\n|align=\"center\" style=\"background:#afeeee;\"|[[1994 European Open (snooker)|1R]]\n| style=\"text-align:center; color:#ccc;\"|LQ\n|align=\"center\" style=\"background:#afeeee;\"|[[1997 European Open (snooker)|2R]]\n| style=\"text-align:center; color:#ccc;\"|NH\n|align=\"center\" style=\"background:#afeeee;\"|[[1998 Irish Open|1R]]\n| align=\"center\" colspan=\"2\" style=\"color:#cccccc;\"| Not Held\n| style=\"text-align:center; color:#ccc;\"|LQ\n| style=\"text-align:center; color:#ccc;\"|LQ\n| style=\"text-align:center; color:#ccc;\"|LQ\n|-\n|style=\"background:#EFEFEF;\" | [[Irish Masters]]\n|align=\"center\" colspan=\"15\" style=\"color:#cccccc;\"| Non-Ranking Event\n| style=\"text-align:center; color:#ccc;\"|LQ\n| style=\"text-align:center; color:#ccc;\"|WD\n|-\n|style=\"background:#EFEFEF;\" | [[Scottish Open (snooker)|Players Championship]]<ref group=\"nb\" >The event ran under different names such as International Open (1987/1988 to 1996/1997).</ref>\n| style=\"text-align:center; color:#ccc;\"|A\n|align=\"center\" style=\"background:#afeeee;\"|[[1988 International Open|2R]]\n|align=\"center\" style=\"background:yellow;\"|[[1989 International Open|SF]]\n|align=\"center\" colspan=\"2\